== Japanese content ==
'''Kagamitsukuri Ita Shrine''' (かがみつくりいたじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Tawaramoto|Q1203159|qid=Q1203159|1=Tawaramoto, Nara}}, {{ill|lt=Shiki District|Q1155036|qid=Q1155036|1=Shiki District, Nara}}, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|qid=Q131287|1=Nara Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}} in Shiroshita District of {{ill|lt=Yamato Province|Q907495|qid=Q907495|1=Yamato Province}} listed in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}, and in adjoining settlements of the same town there are two shrines regarded as candidate sites.

=== Kagamitsukuri Ita Shrine (Miyako) ===

{{神社
|名称=Kagamitsukuri Ita Shrine
|画像=[[File:Kahamitsukuri Ita Shaden.jpg|270px]]<br />Shrine buildings<br />{{maplink2|frame=yes|plain=yes|type=point|marker=religious-shinto|zoom=13|frame-align=center|frame-width=270}}
|緯度度 = 34 | 緯度分 = 33 | 緯度秒 = 30 | N(北緯)及びS(南緯) = N
|経度度 = 135 |経度分 = 46 | 経度秒 = 58 | E(東経)及びW(西経) = E
|ラベル位置 = top
