=== Overview ===
It is enshrined at the south end of the Miyako settlement, west of Miyako Pond. Miyako belonged to {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shiroshita District|1=UNKNOWN}} since ancient times; while early history is unknown, it is thought that the Miyake no Muraji clan of this area enshrined their ancestral deity. It was formerly called Hoya Myōjin.

=== Precinct ===
The current shrine buildings were rebuilt after typhoon damage in {{ill|lt=Heisei|Q234510|qid=Q234510|1=Heisei era}} 9 ({{ill|lt=1997|Q2088|qid=Q2088|1=1997}}). The honden is an ikken-sha {{ill|lt=nagare-zukuri|Q210684|qid=Q210684|1=Nagare-zukuri}} with chigi and katsuogi.

<gallery>
ファイル:Kagamitsukuri Ita Miyako Torii.jpg|Haiden
ファイル:Kagamitsukuri Ita Miyako Honden.jpg|Honden
</gallery>

=== Local information ===
; Location
*{{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|qid=Q131287|1=Nara Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Shiki District|Q1155036|qid=Q1155036|1=Shiki District, Nara}}{{ill|lt=Tawaramoto|Q1203159|qid=Q1203159|1=Tawaramoto, Nara}}Miyako, Aza Hoya 60

; Access
* About 15 minutes on foot northwest from {{ill|lt=Tawaramoto Station|Q7689224|qid=Q7689224|1=Tawaramoto Station}} on the {{ill|lt=Kintetsu|Q1531085|qid=Q1531085|lt=Kintetsu|1=Kintetsu Railway}} {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Kashihara Line|1=UNKNOWN}}

=== External links ===
*[https://narayado.info/nara/kagamitsukuri-ita.html Kagamitsukuri Ita Shrine @ Miyako, Tawaramoto]

=== Kagamitsukuri Ita Shrine (Hozu) ===

{{神社
|名称=Kagamitsukuri Ita Shrine (Hozu)
|画像= {{画像募集中|cat=磯城郡}}
